// Package host is minbasic's I/O delegate — the ONE place that reaches
// pkg/bootstrap. It binds the engine's output to the process's standard streams,
// so the interpreter core never touches an fd. When pkg/bootstrap is eventually
// removed/renamed, only this package changes.
package "pkg/host"

// WriteOut sends the characters of s to standard output with no added newline
// (so PRINT's trailing-';' suppression and inline prompts work later). Returns
// the number of characters written.
//
// TEMP: the core calls this STATIC function directly. The intended design injects
// an io.ConsoleOut into the engine, but that path currently miscompiles — calling
// an interface method with a 2-word slice arg drops the slice's len word (both
// backends), and the VM also mishandles an injected @func writer (nil vtable).
// See explorations/claude-todo.md. Once both are fixed + released, output routes
// through an injected io.ConsoleOut (a bootstrapConsole impl here) and the core
// stops importing pkg/host.
func WriteOut(s *[]readonly char) int
